WEBVTT

00:05.890 --> 00:06.891
Now's the time.

00:10.174 --> 00:11.315
The time to build.

00:14.739 --> 00:16.460
Not everything that's built endures.

00:17.421 --> 00:19.223
Not everything that's built remains.

00:20.304 --> 00:21.806
Some things fall under pressure.

00:22.666 --> 00:24.228
Some things fade with time.

00:25.769 --> 00:27.691
Will what we build now endure?

00:29.773 --> 00:34.578
Will what we build speak through the next generation.

00:36.098 --> 00:39.884
We must be diligent, determined, and dedicated.

00:40.585 --> 00:45.093
After all, his church must be built to last.

00:47.417 --> 00:49.600
But I'm excited that you're here today.

00:49.660 --> 00:52.986
The heat is on, and that's not just a song from the 80s.

00:54.589 --> 00:55.410
Come on.

00:55.714 --> 01:06.831
I must quote 80s songs a lot, because I had somebody the other day literally send me an 80s song and said, hey, this will be a really good illustration for a sermon since you use 80s songs all the time.

01:08.053 --> 01:10.557
Hey, but 80s was the greatest time in America, right?

01:11.258 --> 01:13.081
Come on, that's up by shaking her head.

01:13.982 --> 01:14.743
Aw, come on now.

01:14.943 --> 01:16.466
We'll pray for you, it'll be okay.

01:16.906 --> 01:24.498
One person just booed that, but I'll tell you what, 80s were great, had an afro in the 80s, had parachute pants, come on, any parachute pants fans?

01:24.802 --> 01:25.684
Come on, I was cool.

01:25.964 --> 01:28.028
I had a white shirt with big old black polka dots.

01:30.833 --> 01:31.895
Man, I was happening.

01:31.915 --> 01:34.339
I actually saw a picture of myself as my mom.

01:34.880 --> 01:40.269
We were going through her stuff several months ago, and going through some pictures, and there was a picture of me with these.

01:40.871 --> 01:41.812
Do you remember jams?

01:42.794 --> 01:49.586
I had a pair of jams that were like multi-color, and I had this really cool little hat, and you know, my son goes, was that a costume?

01:51.618 --> 01:52.639
And I said, I was cool.

01:52.940 --> 01:55.123
The 80s called and they were like, man, you are hip.

01:55.383 --> 01:56.265
You are happening.

01:56.605 --> 01:57.987
Hey, I don't know why I'm telling you all that.

01:58.007 --> 01:59.089
That's a confessional moment.

01:59.109 --> 02:00.190
I feel much better now.

02:01.052 --> 02:03.315
But we can go on with the morning.

02:03.555 --> 02:05.458
I'm honored that you were here today.

02:06.359 --> 02:07.421
My name is Pastor Chris.

02:07.862 --> 02:09.384
You know all about me in the 80s.

02:09.464 --> 02:11.928
So we are best friends now.

02:12.488 --> 02:13.650
Thanks for being here.

02:13.858 --> 02:17.608
If you're a guest or checking things out, you're trying to figure out where you belong.

02:17.648 --> 02:19.312
Maybe you're looking for a church home.

02:19.894 --> 02:22.180
Let me just reiterate what the ladies said a while ago.

02:23.062 --> 02:23.664
Welcome home.

02:24.586 --> 02:25.107
Welcome home.

02:25.147 --> 02:26.130
We are honored.

02:26.210 --> 02:26.992
that you were here.

02:27.012 --> 02:31.641
I would encourage you, get plugged in, get to know those around, introduce yourself.

02:31.661 --> 02:39.176
I know sometimes that's awkward and it's difficult, but the only way that we can truly walk together is if we make ourselves available to walk together.

02:39.857 --> 02:41.861
So let's do that as a church body.

02:41.881 --> 02:44.306
So again, thanks so much.

02:44.642 --> 02:48.110
For being here, those of you that are watching online, we love you as well.

02:48.912 --> 02:50.055
Love to see your face.

02:50.416 --> 02:59.378
We're so honored that you're choosing to pause the chaos of social media just to allow God to speak into your life this morning.

02:59.970 --> 03:09.103
All right, well, we are in part three of a short four week series, five week actually series, that we're calling built to last.

03:09.123 --> 03:21.821
We're taking some time and we're looking at what does it mean to not just build something for the kingdom of God, not just build what God has laid before us, but what does it mean to build it to last?

03:21.881 --> 03:25.106
How have you know there's a difference between the two?

03:27.522 --> 03:28.683
Okay, let me just share with you.

03:28.843 --> 03:30.425
There's a difference between the two.

03:31.646 --> 03:33.448
Yeah, there really, really is.

03:33.548 --> 03:48.722
We were doing some remodel several years ago, and as we were going through one of the rooms, I've told you about one where all the nails were in the platform, but there was another room where there was a sound booth, and we discovered that the sound booth was held to the wall.

03:49.603 --> 03:50.323
You ready for this?

03:51.144 --> 03:52.065
By scotch tape.

03:54.467 --> 03:57.490
We discovered it was not built to last.

03:58.498 --> 04:04.504
Come on, God is calling us not to have a scotch tape relationship with him.

04:05.067 --> 04:07.698
God's calling us to move beyond just

04:07.778 --> 04:24.380
maintaining in the moment and that'll do mentality, God's calling us to a place of building something that will last, building what He's laid upon our heart that will far surpass us, that will move into the next generation.

04:24.741 --> 04:29.527
I love the part of the bumper video where the little one speaks up and that's Evan by the way.

04:29.587 --> 04:37.618
And I love when she says, will we understand, will we believe, will we build something that lasts for the next

04:37.986 --> 04:42.811
generation, and then there's a picture of the young lady kneeling simply worshiping.

04:43.933 --> 04:47.116
Guys, that's why we gather here.

04:48.478 --> 04:56.988
That's why we do what we do here so that we can build into and speak into the next generation.

04:57.788 --> 05:01.032
Now, it's really easy, though, for us to sit back and go, no, no, no, no.

05:01.413 --> 05:03.255
This is all about us.

05:03.375 --> 05:06.258
What's in it for my generation?

05:06.754 --> 05:08.336
And yeah, I agree.

05:08.596 --> 05:11.540
We've got to build for the current generation.

05:12.040 --> 05:16.486
But if that's all we do, then we're failing to fulfill the call of God.

05:16.866 --> 05:25.076
The great commission, we're gonna read it in just a few moments, tells us to go into all the world and share the good news of Christ with everyone everywhere.

05:25.357 --> 05:28.020
I don't think that stops it right here.

05:29.842 --> 05:36.210
But for too many years, we as a church have been guilty of satisfying.

05:36.994 --> 05:38.777
are foreign no more.

05:40.360 --> 05:51.878
We've been satisfied with, is the music the way I like it, is the temperature the way I like it, is the room laid out the way I like it, is anybody sitting in my seat?

05:55.865 --> 05:58.930
We had a gentleman a couple weeks ago, second service,

05:59.138 --> 06:02.882
sat right over here, which is odd, because normally he sits right over here.

06:03.303 --> 06:07.748
But for the last three or four weeks, there hasn't been a spot where he sits over here.

06:07.808 --> 06:13.194
So the second week he sat back there, and then he sat over there, and then a couple weeks ago he was right over here.

06:13.235 --> 06:15.938
And I stopped and I said, man, you're getting to start getting here earlier.

06:16.138 --> 06:19.302
He goes, the great thing is, all these seats sit the same.

06:20.563 --> 06:26.450
And I was like, that's fantastic, because how many times have we seen, oh, not in this church?

06:27.650 --> 06:30.495
But we've seen people walk by and their seats taken.

06:30.595 --> 06:32.318
I know I'm a creature of habit.

06:32.338 --> 06:39.692
I go to conferences, I go to meetings, and I love to sit third row, right side, right off the center.

06:40.433 --> 06:41.575
That's where I like to sit.

06:41.816 --> 06:44.020
That's where I can see the best.

06:44.040 --> 06:45.663
That's kind of my focal point.

06:45.683 --> 06:48.548
If I'm too much closer, my wife doesn't like to be that close.

06:48.949 --> 06:51.954
If I'm too much further back, ADHD kicks in.

06:52.962 --> 06:56.206
Come on and I watch everything going by and I miss what's happening.

06:56.467 --> 07:01.414
So third row is pretty, that's prime real estate and nobody's sitting there this morning.

07:01.714 --> 07:02.435
That's crazy.

07:02.455 --> 07:03.456
You guys are missing out.

07:03.797 --> 07:05.920
Somebody needs to sit right there.

07:06.080 --> 07:07.722
Ron, you guys need to move up one row.

07:07.742 --> 07:09.545
That's the seat.

07:09.565 --> 07:12.929
I know your wife wouldn't do it, but that's the best seat in the house right there.

07:12.949 --> 07:18.817
And I was at a conference a couple of months ago and I walked in and I got there early.

07:18.837 --> 07:22.322
I got there like 30 minutes early because I wanted my seat.

07:25.762 --> 07:29.226
And can I just tell you somebody got there 35 minutes earlier and sat in my seat?

07:31.830 --> 07:34.653
I was like, bro, that's my seat.

07:36.295 --> 07:38.097
We all love our spot.

07:38.738 --> 07:40.160
We love going to the same seat.

07:40.180 --> 07:41.982
We love parking in the same parking spot.

07:42.102 --> 07:43.083
We're creatures of habit.

07:43.284 --> 07:44.806
We like things our way.

07:44.986 --> 07:47.769
We want things just the way we like them.

07:49.772 --> 07:54.898
But what if I was to tell you that God's calling us to something greater

07:55.074 --> 07:56.616
than our personal preference.

08:00.501 --> 08:06.668
Some of you are like, I'm telling you, this is not about us.

08:09.191 --> 08:17.762
This is about the 20,000 people in Pettis County that claim no connection with God whatsoever.

08:18.803 --> 08:21.106
They're deemed as the unreached.

08:22.434 --> 08:27.779
I don't know when we've got kind of politically correct and no longer call them unsaved or unchurched.

08:27.999 --> 08:29.741
They're now called the unreached.

08:30.242 --> 08:32.083
They claim no connection with God.

08:32.103 --> 08:36.588
And in fact, if they were to die today, they would split the gates of hell wide open.

08:36.608 --> 08:51.442
Can I just tell you that we're gathered here today to prepare ourselves, to get ourselves ready, to begin to build that solid foundation so that when we walk outside of these walls, we're ready.

08:52.610 --> 08:55.373
for the mission field.

08:55.393 --> 08:57.936
This is not why Jesus came.

09:00.339 --> 09:05.966
Did you know that there are meetings all over town all week long where you can just kind of go and be a spectator?

09:08.909 --> 09:09.250
It's true.

09:09.990 --> 09:19.762
There are civic clubs all over town that are doing fantastic things, but there's no spiritual substance.

09:21.058 --> 09:22.980
There's no eternal change.

09:23.641 --> 09:27.066
And I'm not speaking against those organizations, they're fantastic.

09:28.408 --> 09:30.931
But that's not the purpose of the church.

09:33.494 --> 09:43.227
We have been called, not just me as the pastor, but we have been called to build something to last.

09:44.468 --> 09:48.914
Something that will far outlast us.

09:49.954 --> 09:55.186
There are people in my life that even when I was a young child, invested in me.

09:56.128 --> 10:04.928
There are people that I can look back to today and I could say, I am who I am today because of them.

10:06.412 --> 10:07.474
This individual.

10:07.746 --> 10:09.508
introduced me to ministry.

10:09.608 --> 10:13.853
This individual set the motion of what it meant to be a follower of Christ.

10:14.194 --> 10:17.177
This individual encouraged me in the process.

10:17.437 --> 10:20.401
This person helped me to become the leader that I am.

10:20.541 --> 10:30.573
If it was not for them investing in something that would last building a foundation in my life, can I just tell you, I wouldn't be here today.

10:33.516 --> 10:35.058
But sometimes we

10:36.258 --> 10:42.044
We see ourselves and we think, I don't know what impact I can make.

10:42.124 --> 10:44.047
I don't really make a difference.

10:44.067 --> 10:55.359
Can I just say that some of these people in my life that's spoken to me, the rest of the church or even the world probably would not have deemed them a leader.

10:57.321 --> 11:05.330
But they took the time because they realized that our relationship with God was more than a scotch tape relationship.

11:06.818 --> 11:18.815
that if we were going to build something that will last, then it's going to take intentionality, it's gonna take hard work, it's gonna take dedication, it's gonna take patience.

11:20.317 --> 11:23.502
Did you know that working with the next generation takes patience?

11:24.664 --> 11:26.046
Come on, somebody.

11:28.289 --> 11:30.392
Man, don't look at the young people in the room.

11:31.994 --> 11:34.578
Man, they think completely different than us, don't they?

11:35.682 --> 11:39.889
Their whole mindset is completely different than us, but that's okay.

11:40.690 --> 11:50.024
Because I'd venture to say that when we were young adults, our generation, the older generation, they would have said, well, those young people today.

11:52.869 --> 12:01.522
They like to take that telephone and go halfway across the house and stretch that cord all out and come back all winding up and craziness, right?

12:01.986 --> 12:04.650
They're not satisfied with three stations on the television.

12:04.691 --> 12:07.035
They don't want to get up and turn the channel themselves.

12:10.360 --> 12:14.707
Come on, some of the young people in the house are going, you used to have to do that.

12:15.909 --> 12:16.671
We did.

12:17.091 --> 12:17.532
We did.

12:17.552 --> 12:19.696
I was the remote control in my house.

12:21.158 --> 12:23.923
I was the one that got that would be like, turn it to channel.

12:24.584 --> 12:25.746
Let's see, we had three.

12:25.858 --> 12:28.523
9 and 13, I think, maybe 4, 9 and 13.

12:28.923 --> 12:31.428
Turn to the channel 9, we won't watch a PBS.

12:31.768 --> 12:33.211
You know, so I was the remote control.

12:33.391 --> 12:35.314
Hey, I haven't gotten into my notes at all yet.

12:35.535 --> 12:38.199
Let me jump right in to this morning.

12:38.259 --> 12:41.204
We are in a series that we're calling built to last.

12:41.224 --> 12:42.086
And here's what I know.

12:42.126 --> 12:49.298
It's important that we understand that the building process includes not only a physical building,

12:49.538 --> 12:55.948
which we're going to do beginning of April, Lord willing, we're gonna break ground right out in this area.

12:56.088 --> 12:58.351
We're gonna put a big old shovel in the ground.

12:58.372 --> 12:59.473
We're gonna dig a hole.

12:59.513 --> 13:01.857
We're gonna have a dedication for that.

13:01.917 --> 13:18.322
We're gonna celebrate that moment, but building his church, that's our theme for the year, building his church is way more than building a grand building for the world to see.

13:20.226 --> 13:39.787
Come on, I walked across the parking lot, the leadership parks across the street, and as I was walking across the parking lot, I was just envisioning a year and a half or so down the road when God blesses us with an incredible venue to reach the 20,000 people.

13:42.310 --> 13:46.194
But what I come to understand is building His church

13:46.882 --> 14:02.559
When Jesus tells us and calls us to build his church, he's not just saying, hey, physically go out and lay a foundation, go out and do the plumbing, do some electrical work, put up some walls, put a roof over the top, insulate it so everybody's nice and toasty.

14:02.879 --> 14:04.941
Make sure there's good lighting and good sound.

14:05.162 --> 14:12.850
He's not talking about that, but what we need to understand is building his church includes what happens inside these walls.

14:14.786 --> 14:21.292
This is the only way that we can radically impact our community for the cause of Christ.

14:21.853 --> 14:26.998
Did you know a physical building will not radically impact eternity?

14:28.499 --> 14:33.244
At least by itself, I've seen some incredible buildings over the years.

14:34.965 --> 14:41.712
I remember as a teenager, actually a college student, I sat in front of the Lincoln Memorial.

14:41.772 --> 14:44.114
What an incredible monument.

14:44.834 --> 14:45.955
sat in front of that thing.

14:45.995 --> 14:49.260
And at that moment in time, I wasn't super emotionally older.

14:49.320 --> 14:50.942
I get the more emotional I get.

14:50.962 --> 14:51.843
I don't understand this.

14:52.143 --> 14:53.405
Somebody needs to explain it to me.

14:54.526 --> 15:00.093
But I remember as a young adult sitting in front of the Lincoln Memorial and just weeping.

15:01.375 --> 15:02.756
But I also realized something.

15:03.718 --> 15:06.541
Yeah, that was a weeping moment, but it didn't change eternity.

15:08.083 --> 15:13.650
What happens inside these walls as we build his church, and that's you,

15:14.434 --> 15:16.997
The Bible says, we are the temple of the Holy Spirit, right?

15:17.598 --> 15:19.259
So we are His church.

15:19.880 --> 15:20.521
I'm His church.

15:20.861 --> 15:21.682
You're His church.

15:22.002 --> 15:22.803
You're His church.

15:23.104 --> 15:23.784
You're His church.

15:23.824 --> 15:25.266
I can go all the way around the room.

15:25.586 --> 15:30.292
Every one of us, we are His church together collectively.

15:31.092 --> 15:34.596
We build something that's going to last.

15:35.658 --> 15:39.522
The question is, are we willing to do the hard work?

15:41.003 --> 15:43.346
If you've ever watched a building begin to go up,

15:43.586 --> 15:45.348
You'll know something interesting happens.

15:47.290 --> 15:50.973
You'll know something's happening, and at first it's not gonna be very impressive.

15:50.993 --> 15:53.075
There's a lot of work that happens below the surface.

15:53.095 --> 15:57.139
There's the footing, the sewer, the water lines, the piping, the list goes on and on.

15:57.320 --> 16:04.907
But I've never seen anybody go by a construction site and go, wow, look at that foundation.

16:08.411 --> 16:11.954
I mean, look at those pipes coming out of the ground.

16:12.130 --> 16:13.451
That's impressive.

16:13.491 --> 16:16.895
Now, there might be one of you in the house today.

16:16.935 --> 16:19.278
You're like, man, I just love a good foundation.

16:19.318 --> 16:21.260
That just really gets me excited.

16:21.280 --> 16:30.510
Now, I've never seen anybody that gets really overwhelmed by the foundation, but without the foundation, nothing else stands.

16:32.252 --> 16:37.938
Let me say that again, without the foundation, nothing else stands.

16:38.882 --> 16:42.727
We've taken the last couple of weeks, we've looked at the plans, we've laid the foundation out today.

16:42.988 --> 16:44.369
I'm gonna look at the structure, why?

16:44.570 --> 16:49.416
Because a church that is built to last is more than just steel beams and drywall.

16:49.797 --> 16:54.804
It's built on people that are serious about their pursuit with Jesus Christ.

16:54.884 --> 16:57.007
Let's take a look at our text today.

16:57.027 --> 17:00.051
It's found in 1 Peter, chapter two.

17:01.312 --> 17:07.521
Beginning verse four, he says this, you are coming to Christ who is the living cornerstone.

17:08.022 --> 17:08.402
Come on.

17:09.026 --> 17:12.391
He's the living cornerstone of God's temple.

17:12.411 --> 17:15.856
We're gonna talk more about that than I have throughout this series already.

17:16.556 --> 17:21.744
He was rejected by people, but he was chosen by God for great honor.

17:22.425 --> 17:28.113
And you are living stones that God is building into his spiritual temple.

17:28.173 --> 17:29.014
Come on, did you see that?

17:29.775 --> 17:32.619
You, come on, look at your neighbor say that, includes you.

17:33.981 --> 17:35.903
Put in the chat today, that includes me.

17:35.944 --> 17:37.746
You.

17:38.690 --> 17:44.663
are living stones that God is building into his spiritual temple.

17:44.683 --> 17:46.948
Come on, you may not have arrived yet.

17:49.093 --> 17:50.516
We're a work in progress.

17:52.020 --> 17:54.866
Come on, sometimes we need a little bit of

17:55.234 --> 18:10.491
honing in, we need a little bit of chipping away, we need a little bit of guidance, we need a level, we need things to be plumbed, we need to make sure that everything is right in place, we're not quite there, but God is building us into something that will last.

18:11.793 --> 18:14.576
What's more, you are His holy priest.

18:17.219 --> 18:23.826
Through the meditation of Jesus Christ, you offer spiritual sacrifices that please God, as the scriptures say,

18:25.026 --> 18:28.851
I am placing a cornerstone in Jerusalem chosen for great honor.

18:28.932 --> 18:31.535
And anyone who trusts in him will never be disgraced.

18:31.896 --> 18:36.482
Yes, you who trust him recognize the honor God has given him.

18:36.863 --> 18:43.332
But for those who rejected him, the stone that the builders rejected has now become the cornerstone.

18:43.793 --> 18:49.301
And he is the stone that makes people stumble, the rock that makes them fall.

18:50.282 --> 18:52.946
They stumble because they do not obey God's word.

18:53.698 --> 18:56.182
And so they meet the fate that was planned for them.

18:57.063 --> 18:58.325
But you are not like that.

18:59.146 --> 19:01.690
You were a chosen people.

19:02.491 --> 19:04.034
Come on, I want you to understand this today.

19:04.835 --> 19:07.118
God has called you out.

19:09.021 --> 19:13.789
The Bible says that even while you were yet in your mama's belly, he knew you by name.

19:15.111 --> 19:17.494
You are a chosen people.

19:17.534 --> 19:20.318
You are a royal priest and a holy nation.

19:20.579 --> 19:22.642
God's very own possession.

19:24.738 --> 19:32.626
As a result, you can show others the goodness of God, for he called you out of darkness and into his wonderful light.

19:33.527 --> 19:38.832
Once you had no identity as people, now you are God's people.

19:39.172 --> 19:41.054
Come on, that's good news right there, amen?

19:41.694 --> 19:48.962
You had no idea you were a nobody before, but yet God has made you a somebody.

19:49.122 --> 19:53.586
Once you received no mercy, now you have received God's

19:54.594 --> 19:55.135
Mercy.

19:55.636 --> 19:59.822
Here's a statement I want you to grab a hold of that we're going to build upon today.

20:00.623 --> 20:02.947
Jesus is the living stone.

20:02.967 --> 20:07.474
And because He is the living stone, we are living stones.

20:08.956 --> 20:11.260
And we've been called to build His church.

20:12.842 --> 20:17.028
Take a look at this this morning as we look at four truths to remember.

20:17.048 --> 20:17.930
Are you ready for them today?

20:19.172 --> 20:20.754
Come on, are you ready for them today?

20:21.410 --> 20:26.896
Truth number one is this, everything rises or falls on the cornerstone.

20:28.278 --> 20:35.185
If the cornerstone isn't put in proper position, the rest of the build will not work.

20:35.766 --> 20:38.910
Again, I've talked about some of these things, but why am I repeating it?

20:39.090 --> 20:41.072
Well, Sesame Street repeats itself, right?

20:42.754 --> 20:44.396
Why does Sesame Street repeat itself?

20:44.676 --> 20:46.398
Because our forgetters better?

20:46.438 --> 20:50.002
Come on, sometimes we forget

20:50.498 --> 20:54.864
We try to build things on ourselves, not you all.

20:55.125 --> 20:59.111
I mean, none of you would ever lean upon your own understanding.

20:59.351 --> 21:02.496
